Yobe state Governor, Mai Mala Buni, has charged Catholic Relief Services (CRS) to promote human development by responding to major emergencies, fighting disease and poverty in the  state. The Governor made the call during a courtesy paid on him by the staff of CRS, led by head officer, Yobe, Haruna Sani at Government House Damaturu, the capital. The governor was represented by his Deputy, Hon. Idi Barde Gubana (Wazirin Fune), who commended the activities of donor agencies towards improvement of lives of people of the state and Nigeria at large. According to him, government is committed and ready to partner with any Developmental Agency for the well being  of citizens in the state. He said this would help to promote peace and unity among the people of the state. In his remark, the leader of the delegation, Haruna Sani, who is also Head officer, in the state, disclosed that CRS is the International Humanitarian Agency of the Catholic community in the state which helps the poor and vulnerable overseas. He said that Catholic as one of the efficient organizations in the world, solicited for the support and commitment of the state to enable them deliver on their missions and services effectively. He therefore said the CRS would embark on water and  agriculture projects in Jakusko and Bursari Local Government Areas targeting 1, 500 herders and 1, 500 farmers, as well as stabilization and reconciliation in the Lake Chad region.